metadata.description: CIC ID assigned to the individual; serves as a unique reference for tracking immigration cases.
Year of immigration event; Indicates the year when the immigration record was created.
Identifier for the city where the immigration event took place.
Code representing the country of residence for the individual entering the country.
Code representing the port of entry for the immigration event.
Unique identifier for the date of arrival, used for tracking immigration events.
Identifier for the mode of entry into the country; Indicates how the individual arrived.
Code representing the address associated with the individual; Typically used for location tracking.
Unique identifier for the departure date of the individual; Used to track when the individual left the country.
Indicator of the individual's gender; Uses values to represent Male or Female.
Unique identifier for the type of visa issued to the individual.
Number of entries recorded for the individual in the immigration dataset.
Identifier for the data file associated with the immigration record.
Code representing the visa processing location.
Flag indicating whether the individual has arrived; Typically marked as 'G' for arrival.
Indicates whether the individual has departed from the country.
Flag indicating if the individual's information has been updated.
Indicates whether the immigration record matches with other data sources.
Year of birth of the individual; Used to determine age.
Date when the individual departed; The format is YYYYMMDD.
Gender of the individual; Represented as 'M' for Male and 'F' for Female.
Unique identifier assigned by the Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS) for tracking immigration records.
Code representing the airline used for travel, typically a 2-3 letter abbreviation.
Unique identifier assigned to each admission record for tracking purposes.
Flight number associated with the immigration entry, indicating the specific flight taken.
